        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Like other common nouns, <g>latha</g> can occur with a <a
                    href="?xx=nouns/determiners">determiner</a> as pre-specifier.</p>
            <p>Examples with the <a href="?xx=nouns/definite_article">definite article</a> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil <m>an latha</m> fuar?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the day cold?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt. An robh e anns an
                            sgoil an diugh? Cha robh, bha e anns an taigh fad <m>an latha</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore. Was he in the school
                            today? No, he was in the house all day long.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="deps-mods">
            <h>modifiers</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>latha</g> can occur with an (attributive) <a
                    href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a> (post-)modifier.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>latha math</m> ann an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>It’s a good day today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 12</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>latha brèagha blàth</m> ann.</gd>
                        <tr>It is a beautiful warm day.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [228] [adapted spelling]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>latha</g> can be used as the subject of a <a
                    href="?xx=verbs/verbs">verb</a>.</p>
            <p>Examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>latha</m> math ann an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>It’s a good day today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 12</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an <m>latha</m> fuar?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the day cold?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
