        <section id="uses-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>latha</g> can be used as the specifier of another noun.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt. An robh e anns an
                            sgoil an diugh? Cha robh, bha e anns an taigh fad <m>an latha</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore. Was he in the school
                            today? No, he was in the house all day long.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh an clachair ag obair air a’ bhalla fad an <m>latha</m> an dé?
                            Bha.</gd>
                        <tr>Was the mason working on the wall all day yesterday? Yes, he was.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>

    </section>



